This is the 'datatools' package README file
 
1 - Description:

  This package provides some tool classes for data analysis.
    
  SVN repository:

   * https://nemo.lpc-caen.in2p3.fr/svn/datatools/trunk

   * https://nemo.lpc-caen.in2p3.fr/svn/datatools/tags/datatools-1.0
    
   * https://nemo.lpc-caen.in2p3.fr/svn/datatools/tags/datatools-2.0
    
   * https://nemo.lpc-caen.in2p3.fr/svn/datatools/tags/datatools-2.1
    

  This package depends on the 'boost' C++ library through 
  the 'boost_help' package available at:

   * https://nemo.lpc-caen.in2p3.fr/svn/boost_help/


  WARNING:

  From version 2.0, 'datatools' depends also on the 'pba_help' package
  available at:

   * https://nemo.lpc-caen.in2p3.fr/svn/pba_help/
  For version 2.1, 'datatools' depends on the 'pba_help' package
  but this dependency can be skipped on demand at configuration stage.



2 - Documentation:

  Nothing for now but sample programs are stored in the 'programs'
  directory.
 
3 - Quick start:

  Please install the 'boost_help' package first.

  Configure:

    shell> ./pkgtools.d/pkgtool configure [OPTION]

    With 'pba_help' support (this is the default):

	shell> ./pkgtools.d/pkgtool configure --with-pba

    Without 'pba_help' support:

	shell> ./pkgtools.d/pkgtool configure --without-pba


  Build shared library:

    shell> ./pkgtools.d/pkgtool build


  Build sample programs:

    shell> ./pkgtools.d/pkgtool build bin


  Installation:

    shell> ./pkgtools.d/pkgtool install


  Setup script:

    shell> source datatools.(c)sh


  Run sample program:

    shell> ./Linux-i686/bin/test_tree_dump 


  Uninstall:

    shell> ./pkgtools.d/pkgtool uninstall


  Clean built stuff:

    shell> ./pkgtools.d/pkgtool clean

   
